- "active courses" are courses where the `is_active` flag is set to 1;
- "above-average entry scores" refers to courses with a `clearly_in_atar` score higher than the average ATAR score of all courses.

sql:
SELECT AVG(T2.average_atar) AS average_atar_round_2
FROM rounds AS T1
INNER JOIN offer_statistics AS T2 ON T1.round_id = T2.round_id
WHERE T1.round_name = 'Round 2' AND T2.average_atar > (
    SELECT AVG(average_atar) FROM offer_statistics
);

